============================================================================
Titolo:    Phase transitions and configuration space topology

The configuration space of a classical Hamiltonian system is foliated
in a natural way into a family of equipotential manifolds. Preliminary
results led to conjecture a relationship between a thermodynamical phase
transition and a suitable change of the topology of the equipotential
manifolds. Such a relationship will be investigated within the framework
of Morse theory and the by the direct computation of topological invariants
(like the Euler characteristic) for some model displaying a phase transition.

=============================================================================

